The spread of viruses and ideas can essentially be modeled the same way. Ideas can also spread like viruses, through propaganda, which disseminates facts, ideas, views, arguments in order to shape public opinion. For example, a clear example of spreading ideas through propaganda, is the Communist propaganda in the Soviet Union-propaganda of communist ideas and the Soviet way of life. Propaganda was carried out through the mass media, books, films, theatrical productions, and works of fine art. The purpose of this propaganda was to create a new individual, following the principles of collectivism, voluntarily subordinating his/her interests to those of society and ready to sacrifice himself for the good of society. This is a clear example of how ideas can spread like viruses and influence people through the propaganda

